title: For Sale:  1777 Charleville Carbine - New - $465
postcontent:
The 1777 Charleville carbine was a much-needed improvement for the French cavalry units, and saw fairly mass production, with tens of thousands being produced over the years. Cahmbered in 65 caliber, these musketoons saw service with various armies right into the Napoleonic Wars, and beyond in certain colonial states.
 
    The 1777 musketoon shares many traits with its more famous cousin, the M1777 French Infantry Pattern musket (aka, the Charleville). Rather than steel barrel bands, brass was chosen to further highlight cavalry units as elite. A shortened 34" barrel makes this much lighter and easier to wield than a traditional musket, making it especially popular with smaller frame shooters (if you have family who are intimidated by large muskets, this is the firearm for them).
 
   I do not have bayonets, but they do feature a bayonet lug to mount a standard Bayonet, found at just about any shop (Loyalist comes to mind as a cheap option).Price is firm and is well below shop prices. At the moment these sell for $600+ in shops. The only difference between myself and the shops is: I don't stain your stock, I don't clean your firearm. Most people seem to think the afternoon of very basic work is worth saving $150, per firearm.
 
 
Important Information:
 
-Everything ships via USPS Priority Ground and arrives within 7 days.
-Every firearm comes with a small gift as a thank you; let me know if you want historical or practical.
-These are 90% complete kits. While they are range-ready right out of the box, a deep cleaning and staining of the stock to a proper walnut color is highly recommended. You will notice an immediate improvement once you clean your lock's innards.I have other models, including a flash sale on 1842 Springfields. Email me anytime.
